==English==
===Expression===
'''have a nice day'''

#(''especially US'') [[Goodbye]].

====Usage note====
'''Have a nice day''' is used a [[salutation]] in the same way as '''goodbye'''.  Despite its apparent sentiment, the phrase does not usually convey a wish that the person to whom it is addressed actually have a nice day.

